definition: Eating, Living, Traveling as a foreign student in Okinawa, Japan.
helloはいたい haitai: hello, used by females
I will eat well! (said before eating)
Thank you for the meal (said after eating)
words for happiness, auspiciousness.  Also a word to pray for the safety of the trip, so it is often used in ferry boat names and sightseeing spots.
makers (youkai), similar to menehune in Hawai’i
Okinawa mischief-makers (youkai), similar to menehune in Hawai’i
Once we meet and talk, we are brothers and sisters.
no-eki (Roadside market in Onna Village), chock full of new uchinaaguchi for me to learn!
